---
description: Prevent boilerplate AI attribution text in commits or PRs
alwaysApply: true
---

# No "made with cursor" attribution

- Do not add phrases like "made with cursor", "generated by cursor", or similar AI attribution boilerplate in commit messages, pull request titles, pull request bodies, or repository files unless explicitly requested by the user.
- Keep commit and PR descriptions focused on the actual technical changes and rationale.
